content:
This file provides a collection of reusable React components designed for modern, animated user interfaces, particularly for sign-in forms. It includes animated input fields, labels, box reveal effects, ripple animations, orbiting circles for visual flair, and a complete animated form component.

## Key Exports:

*   **`Input`**: An animated input component with a radial gradient effect on hover/focus.
*   **`Label`**: A standard label component.
*   **`BoxReveal`**: A component that animates its children with a sliding box effect upon entering the viewport.
*   **`Ripple`**: A component that displays a series of concentric, animated ripple circles.
*   **`OrbitingCircles`**: A component that positions its children in an orbiting motion around a central point, optionally with a visible path.
*   **`TechOrbitDisplay`**: A component that displays a logo or text and arranges a set of provided icons in orbiting patterns.
*   **`AnimatedForm`**: A comprehensive form component that includes animated headers, input fields, error handling, social login buttons (e.g., Google), and submit buttons. It supports layout customization with `fieldPerRow`.
*   **`BottomGradient`**: A helper component for creating subtle gradient effects on buttons.

## Usage Example (`AnimatedForm`):

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { AnimatedForm, Input, Label, BoxReveal } from '@/components/ui/modern-animated-sign-in';

const SignInForm = () => {
  const [email, setEmail] = useState('');
  const [password, setPassword] = useState('');

  const handleSubmit = (event) => {
    event.preventDefault();
    console.log('Email:', email);
    console.log('Password:', password);
    // Handle sign-in logic here
  };

  const handleGoToSignUp = () => {
    console.log('Navigating to Sign Up');
    // Navigation logic here
  };

  return (
    <AnimatedForm
      header="Welcome Back!"
      subHeader="Sign in to your account to continue."
      fields={[
        {
          label: 'Email',
          required: true,
          type: 'email',
          placeholder: 'your.email@example.com',
          onChange: (e) => setEmail(e.target.value),
        },
        {
          label: 'Password',
          required: true,
          type: 'password',
          placeholder: '••••••••',
          onChange: (e) => setPassword(e.target.value),
        },
      ]}
      submitButton="Sign In"
      googleLogin="Sign in with Google"
      onGoogleLogin={() => console.log('Google login clicked')}
      textVariantButton="Don't have an account? Sign Up"
      goTo={handleGoToSignUp}
      onSubmit={handleSubmit}
      fieldPerRow={1}
    />
  );
};

export default SignInForm;
```
